oc:kn_16ea641d a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:WorkflowStrategy ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When performing full analysis or formal report" ;
    oc:directiveContent "For complex analyses, break the problem into sub-questions and address each separately. Compare across dimensions (time periods, segments, categories). Lead with the key finding." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Decomposition prevents cognitive overload and ensures comprehensive coverage; leading with findings respects the reader's attention." .

oc:kn_5fe36911 a oc:AntiPattern,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When presenting any findings" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Never present raw query results without validation. Always flag caveats and data quality issues explicitly." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Unvalidated results erode trust; caveats provide essential context for correct interpretation." ;
    oc:severityLevel "MEDIUM" .

oc:kn_70719969 a oc:Constraint,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "After analysis, before presenting findings" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Always run validation checks before presenting results: row count sanity, null check, magnitude check, trend continuity, and aggregation logic verification." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Unchecked results can propagate errors to stakeholders; validation catches data quality issues and logic mistakes before they reach decision-makers." ;
    oc:severityLevel "HIGH" .

oc:kn_a6b98fc7 a oc:Heuristic,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When no connected data source is available" ;
    oc:directiveContent "When no data warehouse MCP is connected, ask the user to paste results, upload CSV/Excel, or describe the schema. Use the sql-queries skill for dialect-specific query writing for manual execution." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Analysis should not be blocked by infrastructure; providing multiple fallback paths ensures progress." .

oc:kn_c5a07acf a oc:KnowledgeNode,
        oc:RecoveryTactic ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When query execution fails or returns unexpected results" ;
    oc:directiveContent "If a query fails, debug by checking column names, table references, and dialect-specific syntax, then retry. If results look unexpected, run sanity checks before proceeding." ;
    oc:hasRationale "SQL failures are commonly caused by dialect differences or schema mismatches; systematic debugging avoids repeated failures." .

oc:kn_cc802e09 a oc:DesignPrinciple,
        oc:KnowledgeNode ;
    oc:appliesToContext "When receiving any data question" ;
    oc:directiveContent "Classify every data question into one of three complexity levels before proceeding: Quick Answer (single metric/lookup), Full Analysis (multi-dimensional/trend), or Formal Report (comprehensive with methodology and recommendations)." ;
    oc:hasRationale "Complexity level determines the depth of gathering, analysis, validation, and presentation — preventing both under-analysis and over-engineering." .

